39
00:04:01.575 --> 00:04:03.999
Dohaeras. Syrax!

40
00:04:08.039 --> 00:04:09.082
Umbas.

41
00:04:10.563 --> 00:04:11.606
Rybas!

42
00:04:23.585 --> 00:04:25.366
Welcome back. Princess.

43
00:04:25.390 --> 00:04:26.835
I trust your ride was pleasant.

44
00:04:26.892 --> 00:04:28.911
Try not to look too relieved. ser.

45
00:04:28.935 --> 00:04:30.436
I am relieved.

46
00:04:30.520 --> 00:04:31.646
Every time that golden beast

47
00:04:31.729 --> 00:04:33.332
brings you back unspoiled.

48
00:04:33.356 --> 00:04:35.467
it saves my head from a spike.

49
00:04:36.968 --> 00:04:38.588
Syrax is growing quickly.

50
00:04:38.612 --> 00:04:40.548
She'll soon be as large as Caraxes.

51
00:04:40.572 --> 00:04:42.675
That's almost large
enough to saddle two.

52
00:04:42.699 --> 00:04:45.769
I believe I'm quite content
as a spectator. thank you.

53
00:04:48.955 --> 00:04:50.891
Dohaeras.

54
00:04:52.186 --> 00:04:53.251
Naejot!

55
00:06:19.866 --> 00:06:22.493
Ah... Rhaenyra.

56
00:06:24.780 --> 00:06:26.653
You know I don't like you to go flying

57
00:06:26.677 --> 00:06:28.155
while I'm in this condition.

58
00:06:28.179 --> 00:06:30.829
You don't like me to go flying
while you're in any condition.

59
00:06:32.378 --> 00:06:35.353
- Your Grace.
- Good morrow. Alicent.

60
00:06:35.545 --> 00:06:36.755
Did you sleep?

61
00:06:36.838 --> 00:06:38.965
- I slept.
- How long?

62
00:06:39.883 --> 00:06:42.290
I don't need mothering. Rhaenyra.

63
00:06:42.360 --> 00:06:44.596
Well. here you are.
surrounded by attendants.

64
00:06:44.679 --> 00:06:46.473
all focused on the babe.

65
00:06:46.890 --> 00:06:48.808
Someone has to attend to you.

66
00:06:50.435 --> 00:06:54.648
You will lie in this bed
soon enough. Rhaenyra.

67
00:06:54.731 --> 00:06:58.318
This discomfort is how
we serve the realm.

68
00:06:58.401 --> 00:07:01.488
I'd rather serve as a knight
and ride to battle and glory.

69
00:07:04.449 --> 00:07:06.826
We have royal wombs. you and I.

70
00:07:08.536 --> 00:07:10.622
The child bed is our battlefield.

71
00:07:12.501 --> 00:07:15.001
We must learn to face it
with a stiff lip.

72
00:07:16.920 --> 00:07:18.547
Now take a bath.

73
00:07:18.922 --> 00:07:20.757
You stink of dragon.

74
00:07:23.093 --> 00:07:26.346
So. I said to him. "Well. I believe
you might be looking up the wrong end."

75
00:07:30.433 --> 00:07:31.601
My lords.

76
00:07:31.935 --> 00:07:33.937
The growing alliance
among the Free Cities

77
00:07:34.020 --> 00:07:36.982
has taken to styling
itself "the Triarchy."

78
00:07:37.065 --> 00:07:39.207
They have massed on Bloodstone

79
00:07:39.292 --> 00:07:41.187
and are presently ridding the Step stones

80
00:07:41.211 --> 00:07:42.529
of its pirate infestation.

81
00:07:42.612 --> 00:07:44.148
Well. that sounds suspiciously

82
00:07:44.172 --> 00:07:45.382
like good news. Lord Corlys.

83
00:07:45.465 --> 00:07:47.525
A man called Craghas Drahar

84
00:07:47.550 --> 00:07:50.553
has styled himself the
prince-admiral of this Triarchy.

85
00:07:51.830 --> 00:07:53.790
They call him "The Crabfeeder"

86
00:07:54.082 --> 00:07:57.002
due to his inventive methods
of punishing his enemies.

87
00:07:57.085 --> 00:07:59.379
And are we meant
to weep for dead pirates?

88
00:08:00.171 --> 00:08:02.806
- No. Your Grace.
- Rhaenyra. you're late.

89
00:08:02.899 --> 00:08:04.551
King's cupbearer must not be late.

90
00:08:04.634 --> 00:08:07.595
- Leaves people wanting for cups.
- I was visiting Mother.

91
00:08:08.555 --> 00:08:11.391
On dragon back?

92
00:08:11.683 --> 00:08:14.552
Hey. Your Grace.
at Prince Daemon's urging.

93
00:08:14.577 --> 00:08:17.247
the crown has invested
significant capital

94
00:08:17.330 --> 00:08:20.708
in the re-training and
re-equipping of his City Watch.

95
00:08:20.784 --> 00:08:22.937
I thought you might urge your brother

96
00:08:22.961 --> 00:08:24.939
to fill his seat on the council

97
00:08:24.963 --> 00:08:27.858
and provide an assessment
of his progress

98
00:08:27.882 --> 00:08:29.944
as commander of the Watch.

99
00:08:29.968 --> 00:08:32.637
Do you think Daemon is
distracted by his present tasks?

100
00:08:32.720 --> 00:08:34.681
And that his thoughts
and energies are occupied?

101
00:08:34.764 --> 00:08:37.952
Well. one would hope so.
considering the associated costs.

102
00:08:37.976 --> 00:08:40.937
Then let us all consider your
gold well-invested. Lord Beesbury.

103
00:08:41.338 --> 00:08:43.206
I would urge that you not allow

104
00:08:43.231 --> 00:08:44.691
this Triarchy much latitude

105
00:08:44.774 --> 00:08:46.384
in the Step stones. Your Grace.

106
00:08:46.801 --> 00:08:48.528
If those shipping lanes should fall.

107
00:08:48.611 --> 00:08:50.113
it will beggar our ports.

108
00:08:50.196 --> 00:08:52.824
The crown has heard
your report. Lord Corlys.

109
00:08:52.907 --> 00:08:54.809
and takes it under advisement.

110
00:09:00.032 --> 00:09:03.610
Shall we discuss the Heir's
Tournament. Your Grace?

111
00:09:04.110 --> 00:09:05.862
I would be delighted.

112
00:09:06.488 --> 00:09:08.840
Will the maesters' name day
prediction hold. Mellos?

113
00:09:08.923 --> 00:09:10.633
You must understand that these things

114
00:09:10.717 --> 00:09:12.427
are mere estimations. my King.

115
00:09:12.510 --> 00:09:13.945
but we have all been...

116
00:09:13.970 --> 00:09:15.638
poring over the moon charts.

117
00:09:15.722 --> 00:09:17.640
and we feel that our forecast

118
00:09:17.724 --> 00:09:19.684
is as accurate as it can be.

119
00:09:19.767 --> 00:09:22.495
The cost of the
tournament is not negligible.

120
00:09:22.527 --> 00:09:26.441
Perhaps we might delay
until the child is in hand?

121
00:09:26.561 --> 00:09:28.599
Ugh. most of the lords and knights

122
00:09:28.624 --> 00:09:31.088
are certainly on their way to King's
Landing already. To turn them back now...

123
00:09:31.112 --> 00:09:33.215
The tourney will
take the better part of a week.

124
00:09:33.239 --> 00:09:35.650
Before the games are over.
my son will be born.

125
00:09:36.059 --> 00:09:37.887
and the whole realm will celebrate.

126
00:09:37.911 --> 00:09:39.847
We have no way of predicting

127
00:09:39.871 --> 00:09:41.140
the sex of the child.

128
00:09:41.164 --> 00:09:42.930
Of course. no maester's capable

129
00:09:43.014 --> 00:09:44.140
of rendering an opinion

130
00:09:44.223 --> 00:09:45.860
free of conditions. are they now?

131
00:09:46.444 --> 00:09:48.446
There's a boy in the Queen's belly.

132
00:09:49.322 --> 00:09:50.448
I know it.

133
00:09:51.825 --> 00:09:54.200
And my heir will soon
put all of this damnable

134
00:09:54.225 --> 00:09:56.246
hand-wringing to rest himself.

135
00:09:59.249 --> 00:10:01.786
He passed through the Red
Keep's gates at first light.

136
00:10:01.810 --> 00:10:03.269
Does my father know he's here?

137
00:10:03.461 --> 00:10:04.838
- No.
- Good.

138
00:10:12.900 --> 00:10:14.986
Gods be good.

139
00:10:15.194 --> 00:10:16.779
It's all right. ser.

140
00:10:25.394 --> 00:10:27.686
_

141
00:10:27.710 --> 00:10:29.141
_

142
00:10:29.530 --> 00:10:32.316
_

143
00:10:32.340 --> 00:10:34.712
_

144
00:10:35.836 --> 00:10:38.679
_

145
00:10:38.799 --> 00:10:39.782
Aye...

146
00:10:39.806 --> 00:10:42.684
_

147
00:10:43.510 --> 00:10:45.854
_

148
00:10:46.137 --> 00:10:49.858
_

149
00:10:50.188 --> 00:10:52.012
_

150
00:10:52.437 --> 00:10:53.437
Mm...

151
00:10:53.706 --> 00:10:55.502
_

152
00:10:56.806 --> 00:10:59.033
_

153
00:10:59.851 --> 00:11:02.729
_

154
00:11:03.563 --> 00:11:05.143
_

155
00:11:05.265 --> 00:11:07.039
_

156
00:11:10.174 --> 00:11:11.654
I bought you something.

157
00:11:17.154 --> 00:11:18.489
Do you know what it is?

158
00:11:19.983 --> 00:11:21.581
It's Valyrian steel.

159
00:11:22.738 --> 00:11:24.438
Like Dark Sister.

160
00:11:28.210 --> 00:11:29.439
Turn around.

161
00:11:44.072 --> 00:11:45.079
Now...

162
00:11:46.379 --> 00:11:49.876
you and I both own a small piece
of our ancestry.

163
00:12:00.234 --> 00:12:01.487
Did you read it?

164
00:12:01.512 --> 00:12:03.014
Of course. I read it.

165
00:12:03.151 --> 00:12:05.618
When Princess
Nymeria arrived in Dorne.

166
00:12:05.642 --> 00:12:07.411
who did she take to husband?

167
00:12:07.435 --> 00:12:08.461
A man.

168
00:12:08.795 --> 00:12:10.255
What was his name?

169
00:12:10.510 --> 00:12:11.981
Lord Something.

170
00:12:12.428 --> 00:12:13.989
If you answer
with "Lord Something."

171
00:12:14.013 --> 00:12:16.002
Septa Marlow will be furious.

172
00:12:16.027 --> 00:12:17.683
She's funny when she's furious.

173
00:12:20.978 --> 00:12:23.242
You're always like this
when you're worried.

174
00:12:23.309 --> 00:12:24.598
Like what?

175
00:12:25.119 --> 00:12:26.526
Disagreeable.

176
00:12:30.465 --> 00:12:32.949
You're worried your father
is about to overshadow you

177
00:12:33.032 --> 00:12:34.045
with a son.

178
00:12:34.367 --> 00:12:36.281
I only worry for my mother.

179
00:12:37.240 --> 00:12:39.534
I hope for my father that he gets a son.

180
00:12:40.285 --> 00:12:42.679
As long as I can recall.
it's all he's wanted.

181
00:12:43.872 --> 00:12:45.456
You want him to have a son?

182
00:12:45.748 --> 00:12:47.992
I want to fly with you on dragon back.

183
00:12:48.017 --> 00:12:50.913
see the great wonders across the
Narrow Sea. and eat only cake.

184
00:12:50.937 --> 00:12:53.339
- I'm being serious.
- I never jest about cake.

185
00:12:53.840 --> 00:12:55.805
You aren't worried about your position?

186
00:12:55.888 --> 00:12:58.094
I like this position.
It's quite comfortable.

187
00:13:02.478 --> 00:13:05.768
- Where are you going?
- Home. The hour has grown late.

188
00:13:06.936 --> 00:13:08.943
Princess Nymeria led her Rhoynar

189
00:13:09.026 --> 00:13:11.195
across the Narrow Sea on 10.000 ships

190
00:13:11.279 --> 00:13:13.239
to flee their Valyrian pursuers.

191
00:13:13.322 --> 00:13:16.200
She took Lord Mors Martell
of Dorne to husband

192
00:13:16.321 --> 00:13:18.327
and burned her own fleet off Sun spear

193
00:13:18.411 --> 00:13:20.496
to show her people that
they were finished running.

194
00:13:22.482 --> 00:13:24.704
- What are you doing?
- So you remember.

195
00:13:25.747 --> 00:13:28.666
- If-if the Septa sees this book. then...
- Fuck the Septa.

196
00:13:29.088 --> 00:13:30.506
Rhaenyra!

197
00:13:43.181 --> 00:13:44.390
Is it healing?

198
00:13:44.641 --> 00:13:47.410
It has grown
slightly. Your Grace.

199
00:13:49.645 --> 00:13:51.606
Can you say yet what it is?

200
00:13:51.778 --> 00:13:54.268
We've sent enquiries to the Citadel.

201
00:13:54.292 --> 00:13:56.437
They are searching
the texts for similar cases.

202
00:13:56.461 --> 00:13:58.939
It's a small cut
from sitting the throne.

203
00:13:58.963 --> 00:14:00.073
It's nothing.

204
00:14:00.740 --> 00:14:02.952
The King has been under heavy stresses

205
00:14:02.976 --> 00:14:04.535
preparing for the birth.

206
00:14:05.495 --> 00:14:07.330
Bad humors of the mind

207
00:14:07.413 --> 00:14:09.582
can adversely affect the body.

208
00:14:10.166 --> 00:14:13.252
Whatever it is.
it needs to be kept quiet.

209
00:14:16.829 --> 00:14:18.542
We should leech it again. maester.

210
00:14:18.566 --> 00:14:21.069
It's a wound that refuses to
heal. Grand Maester.

211
00:14:22.345 --> 00:14:24.263
Might I suggest cauterization?

212
00:14:24.347 --> 00:14:26.120
Cauterization would be a wise

213
00:14:26.144 --> 00:14:27.934
course of treatment. Your Grace.

214
00:14:28.476 --> 00:14:30.317
- It will be painful...
- Fine.

215
00:14:32.105 --> 00:14:33.189
Fine.

216
00:14:46.035 --> 00:14:48.705
You spend more time in that bath
than I do on the throne.

217
00:14:49.359 --> 00:14:50.741
This is the only place

218
00:14:50.765 --> 00:14:52.959
I can find comfort these days.

219
00:14:55.264 --> 00:14:56.629
It's tepid.

220
00:14:56.948 --> 00:14:59.424
It's as warm as the maesters will allow.

221
00:14:59.674 --> 00:15:02.260
- Don't they know dragons prefer heat?
- Hm.

222
00:15:03.094 --> 00:15:05.388
After this miserable pregnancy...

223
00:15:06.139 --> 00:15:09.350
I wouldn't be surprised if
I hatched an actual dragon.

224
00:15:09.600 --> 00:15:11.811
Then he will
be loved and cherished.

225
00:15:12.954 --> 00:15:15.898
Rhaenyra has already declared
that she is to have a sister.

226
00:15:16.232 --> 00:15:17.232
Really?

227
00:15:17.608 --> 00:15:20.570
- She even named her.
- Dare I ask?

228
00:15:21.446 --> 00:15:23.357
Visenya.

229
00:15:23.381 --> 00:15:25.150
She chose a dragon's egg for the cradle

230
00:15:25.174 --> 00:15:26.985
that she said reminded her of Vhagar.

231
00:15:27.009 --> 00:15:28.278
Gods be good.

232
00:15:28.302 --> 00:15:30.747
This family already has its Visenya.

233
00:15:32.857 --> 00:15:35.418
Has there been any word
from your dear brother?

234
00:15:35.626 --> 00:15:38.296
Not since I named him
Commander of the City Watch.

235
00:15:39.047 --> 00:15:41.607
I'm sure he will reemerge
for the tourney.

236
00:15:42.341 --> 00:15:44.510
He could never stay away from the lists.

237
00:15:44.886 --> 00:15:46.095
The tourney...

238
00:15:46.345 --> 00:15:48.090
to celebrate the firstborn son

239
00:15:48.114 --> 00:15:49.866
that we presently do not have.

240
00:15:50.725 --> 00:15:52.185
You do understand

241
00:15:52.435 --> 00:15:54.638
nothing will cause
the babe to grow a cock

242
00:15:54.662 --> 00:15:56.564
if it does not already possess one?

243
00:15:56.814 --> 00:15:59.317
This child is a boy. Aemma.

244
00:15:59.525 --> 00:16:00.943
I'm certain of it.

245
00:16:01.652 --> 00:16:04.113
I've never been more
certain of anything.

246
00:16:07.782 --> 00:16:08.826
The dream.

247
00:16:10.232 --> 00:16:11.913
It was clearer than a memory.

248
00:16:14.445 --> 00:16:17.126
Our son was born wearing
Aegon's iron crown.

249
00:16:19.033 --> 00:16:22.298
And I heard the sound
of thundering hooves.

250
00:16:22.620 --> 00:16:25.093
splintering shields. and ringing swords.

251
00:16:25.927 --> 00:16:28.613
and I placed our son
upon the Iron Throne...

252
00:16:29.941 --> 00:16:31.949
as the bells of the Grand Sept tolled

253
00:16:32.575 --> 00:16:34.727
and all the dragons roared as one.

254
00:16:38.314 --> 00:16:40.191
Born wearing a crown?

255
00:16:40.650 --> 00:16:41.984
Gods spare me...

256
00:16:42.276 --> 00:16:44.529
birth is unpleasant enough as it is.

257
00:16:53.913 --> 00:16:55.706
This is the last time.

258
00:16:56.332 --> 00:16:57.500
Viserys.

259
00:17:00.089 --> 00:17:02.088
I've lost one babe in the cradle.

260
00:17:02.171 --> 00:17:04.173
had two stillbirths. and two pregnancies

261
00:17:04.257 --> 00:17:06.217
ended well before their term.

262
00:17:09.095 --> 00:17:11.973
That's five... in twice as many years.

263
00:17:13.391 --> 00:17:16.102
I know it is my duty
to provide you an heir.

264
00:17:16.477 --> 00:17:19.981
and I'm sorry if I have
failed you in that. I am.

265
00:17:23.693 --> 00:17:26.445
But I've mourned all
the dead children I can.

266
00:17:47.884 --> 00:17:50.178
Commander on the floor!

267
00:17:56.642 --> 00:17:59.912
When I took command of the
Watch. you were stray mongrels...

268
00:18:01.689 --> 00:18:03.900
starving and undisciplined.

269
00:18:05.777 --> 00:18:06.861
Now...

270
00:18:07.184 --> 00:18:09.071
you're a pack of hounds.

271
00:18:09.697 --> 00:18:12.233
You're sated and honed for the hunt.

272
00:18:15.661 --> 00:18:18.831
My brother's city
has fallen into squalor.

273
00:18:20.082 --> 00:18:23.519
Crime of every breed
has been allowed to thrive.

274
00:18:25.546 --> 00:18:26.814
No longer.

275
00:18:27.215 --> 00:18:29.251
Beginning tonight.
King's Landing will learn

276
00:18:29.275 --> 00:18:31.169
to fear the color gold.

277
00:19:16.806 --> 00:19:18.366
Get up!

278
00:19:38.828 --> 00:19:40.179
Raper!

279
00:19:42.832 --> 00:19:45.376
No! No! No! No! No!

280
00:19:52.850 --> 00:19:54.110
Thief!

281
00:19:54.844 --> 00:19:56.178
No!

282
00:20:01.861 --> 00:20:03.436
Murderer!

283
00:20:19.736 --> 00:20:23.114
It was an unprecedented
roundup of criminals of every ilk.

284
00:20:23.139 --> 00:20:25.249
Your brother made a public show of it.

285
00:20:25.333 --> 00:20:27.953
meting out the summary
judgments himself.

286
00:20:27.977 --> 00:20:30.771
I'm told they needed a two-horse cart

287
00:20:31.380 --> 00:20:33.382
to haul away the
resulting dismemberments

288
00:20:33.466 --> 00:20:34.466
when it was done.

289
00:20:34.508 --> 00:20:36.761
Gods be good.

290
00:20:37.345 --> 00:20:39.305
The Prince cannot be allowed to act

291
00:20:39.388 --> 00:20:41.640
with this kind of unchecked impunity.

292
00:20:44.477 --> 00:20:46.312
- Brother.
- Daemon.

293
00:20:47.990 --> 00:20:50.666
Carry on. You were saying
something about my impunity.

294
00:20:53.611 --> 00:20:56.238
You are to explain your doings
with the City Watch.

295
00:20:59.286 --> 00:21:02.612
Your new "gold cloaks" made quite the
impression last night. didn't they?

296
00:21:02.636 --> 00:21:03.931
Did they?

297
00:21:03.955 --> 00:21:05.414
The City Watch is not a sword

298
00:21:05.498 --> 00:21:07.249
to be wielded at your whim.

299
00:21:07.333 --> 00:21:09.335
They're an extension of the crown.

300
00:21:09.418 --> 00:21:11.462
The Watch was enforcing
the crown's laws.

301
00:21:11.545 --> 00:21:13.547
Wouldn't you agree. Lord Strong?

302
00:21:14.340 --> 00:21:18.594
- My Prince. I don't think...
- Making a public spectacle of wanton brutality

303
00:21:18.678 --> 00:21:20.346
is hardly in line with our laws.

304
00:21:20.429 --> 00:21:22.131
Nobles from every corner of the realm

305
00:21:22.156 --> 00:21:24.300
are right now descending
upon King's Landing

306
00:21:24.325 --> 00:21:25.594
for my brother's tourney.

307
00:21:25.618 --> 00:21:28.120
Do you want them
mugged. raped. murdered?

308
00:21:28.248 --> 00:21:31.307
You mightn't know this unless you
left the safety of the Red Keep.

309
00:21:31.332 --> 00:21:33.851
but much of King's Landing
is seen by the small folk

310
00:21:33.876 --> 00:21:36.629
as lawless and terrifying.

311
00:21:38.781 --> 00:21:41.133
Our city should be safe
for all its people.

312
00:21:41.784 --> 00:21:42.952
I agree.

313
00:21:43.577 --> 00:21:45.113
I just hope you don't have to maim

314
00:21:45.137 --> 00:21:47.139
half of my city to achieve this.

315
00:21:47.848 --> 00:21:49.225
Time will tell.

316
00:21:51.752 --> 00:21:55.481
We installed Prince Daemon as
commander to promote law and order.

317
00:21:55.840 --> 00:21:58.342
The criminal element
should fear the City Watch.

318
00:21:58.425 --> 00:22:00.025
Thank you for your support. Lord Corlys.

319
00:22:00.152 --> 00:22:02.054
If only the Prince would
show the same devotion

320
00:22:02.137 --> 00:22:04.848
to his lady wife as he does his
work. Your Grace.

321
00:22:04.932 --> 00:22:06.433
You've not been seen in the Vale

322
00:22:06.517 --> 00:22:08.686
or at Runestone for quite some time.

323
00:22:08.769 --> 00:22:11.222
I think my bronze bitch
is happier for my absence.

324
00:22:11.247 --> 00:22:13.024
Lady Rhea is your wife.

325
00:22:13.165 --> 00:22:15.192
a good and honorable lady of the Vale.

326
00:22:15.275 --> 00:22:17.994
In the Vale. men are said to
fuck sheep instead of women.

327
00:22:18.128 --> 00:22:20.572
I can assure you.
the sheep are prettier.

328
00:22:20.656 --> 00:22:21.656
Dear me.

329
00:22:21.699 --> 00:22:22.992
You made a vow before the Seven

330
00:22:23.075 --> 00:22:24.777
to honor your wife in marriage.

331
00:22:24.802 --> 00:22:26.304
Well. I'd gladly give Lady Rhea to you.

332
00:22:26.328 --> 00:22:27.871
Lord High tower. if you're in want

333
00:22:27.955 --> 00:22:30.082
of a woman to warm your bed.

334
00:22:30.165 --> 00:22:32.641
Your own lady wife passed recently.

335
00:22:35.003 --> 00:22:36.272
Did she not?

336
00:22:36.797 --> 00:22:37.840
Otto.

337
00:22:41.093 --> 00:22:43.470
Perhaps you aren't ready
to move on just yet.

338
00:22:44.305 --> 00:22:47.141
You know how my brother
makes sport of provoking you.

339
00:22:47.808 --> 00:22:49.393
Must you indulge him?

340
00:22:53.397 --> 00:22:55.381
My apologies. Your Grace.

341
00:22:55.541 --> 00:22:58.610
This council
has. at great expense.

342
00:22:58.694 --> 00:23:01.547
bettered the City Watch
to your exacting standards.

343
00:23:01.739 --> 00:23:04.158
Enforce my laws. but understand...

344
00:23:04.617 --> 00:23:07.161
any further performances
like last night's

345
00:23:07.244 --> 00:23:08.328
will be answered.

346
00:23:12.291 --> 00:23:13.626
Understood. Your Grace.

347
00:23:27.531 --> 00:23:30.066
King's Landing has been in decline
since my grandmother passed.

348
00:23:30.444 --> 00:23:31.929
In the end...

349
00:23:33.199 --> 00:23:34.813
this new City Watch

350
00:23:35.105 --> 00:23:36.649
might be a good thing.

351
00:24:22.675 --> 00:24:24.713
What troubles you. my Prince?

352
00:24:31.120 --> 00:24:32.871
I could bring in another.

353
00:24:33.622 --> 00:24:35.207
Perhaps a maiden.

354
00:24:36.250 --> 00:24:37.685
I have several.

355
00:24:39.753 --> 00:24:42.298
I could even arrange one
with silver hair.

356
00:24:48.841 --> 00:24:50.973
You are Daemon Targaryen.

357
00:24:51.599 --> 00:24:54.852
Rider of Caraxes.
Wielder of Dark Sister.

358
00:24:55.394 --> 00:24:57.771
The King cannot replace you.

359
00:25:10.784 --> 00:25:12.261
Be welcome!

360
00:25:13.037 --> 00:25:15.661
I know many of you have
traveled long leagues

361
00:25:15.889 --> 00:25:17.374
to be at these games.

362
00:25:18.000 --> 00:25:21.295
But I promise. you will
not be disappointed.

363
00:25:22.671 --> 00:25:25.299
When I look at the fine
knights in these lists.

364
00:25:25.799 --> 00:25:29.386
I see a group without equal
in our histories.

365
00:25:30.679 --> 00:25:32.640
And this great day

366
00:25:33.182 --> 00:25:35.743
has been made more auspicious

367
00:25:35.976 --> 00:25:37.227
by the news...

368
00:25:37.561 --> 00:25:39.646
that I am happy to share:

369
00:25:40.898 --> 00:25:43.667
Queen Aemma has begun her labors!

370
00:25:47.252 --> 00:25:50.824
May the luck of the Seven
shine upon all combatants!

371
00:26:23.982 --> 00:26:25.692
A mystery knight?

372
00:26:25.776 --> 00:26:27.836
No. a Cole. of the Storm lands.

373
00:26:28.028 --> 00:26:29.404
I've never heard of House Cole.

374
00:26:29.488 --> 00:26:31.865
Princess Rhaenys Targaryen!

375
00:26:32.199 --> 00:26:34.284
I would humbly ask for the favor

376
00:26:34.368 --> 00:26:36.178
of "The Queen Who Never Was."

377
00:26:42.683 --> 00:26:44.369
Good fortune to you. cousin.

378
00:26:44.394 --> 00:26:47.147
I would gladly take it
if I thought I needed it.

379
00:26:53.303 --> 00:26:55.555
You could have
Baratheon's tongue for that.

380
00:26:56.352 --> 00:26:58.575
Tongues will not change the succession.

381
00:26:58.725 --> 00:27:00.102
Let them wag.

382
00:27:06.900 --> 00:27:08.435
Lord Stokeworth's daughter

383
00:27:08.460 --> 00:27:10.266
is promised to that young Tarly squire.

384
00:27:10.291 --> 00:27:11.564
- Lord Massey's son?
- Mm-hm.

385
00:27:11.588 --> 00:27:14.366
They're to be married as soon
as he wins his knighthood.

386
00:27:14.696 --> 00:27:16.760
Best get on with it.

387
00:27:17.246 --> 00:27:20.639
I heard that Lady Elinor is hiding
a swollen belly beneath her dress.

388
00:27:43.604 --> 00:27:46.239
What do you know about this
Ser Criston Cole. Ser Harrold?

389
00:27:46.264 --> 00:27:48.142
I'm told Ser Criston
is common-born.

390
00:27:48.166 --> 00:27:49.840
son of Lord Dondarrion's steward.

391
00:27:49.865 --> 00:27:52.656
But other than that.
and the fact that he's just unhorsed

392
00:27:52.748 --> 00:27:54.423
both of the Baratheon lads.

393
00:27:54.825 --> 00:27:56.234
I really couldn't say.

394
00:28:14.720 --> 00:28:18.349
Prince Daemon of House Targaryen.

395
00:28:18.432 --> 00:28:20.173
Prince of the City.

396
00:28:20.198 --> 00:28:23.737
will now choose his first opponent!

397
00:29:00.933 --> 00:29:03.519
For his first challenge.

398
00:29:03.602 --> 00:29:06.370
Prince Daemon Targaryen chooses

399
00:29:06.854 --> 00:29:09.431
Ser Gwayne High tower of Old town.

400
00:29:09.456 --> 00:29:12.359
eldest son of the Hand of the King.

401
00:29:24.790 --> 00:29:27.084
Five dragons on Daemon.

402
00:29:48.063 --> 00:29:49.565
Ya!

403
00:30:40.324 --> 00:30:43.216
- Nicely done. Uncle.
- Thank you. Princess.

404
00:30:44.493 --> 00:30:48.138
Now. I'm fairly certain I can
win these games. Lady Alicent.

405
00:30:48.332 --> 00:30:51.585
Having your favor
would all but assure it.

406
00:31:05.933 --> 00:31:07.434
Good luck. my Prince.

407
00:31:35.587 --> 00:31:38.413
- What's happening?
- The infant is in breech. Your Grace.

408
00:31:38.438 --> 00:31:40.774
All attempts to turn
the babe have failed.

409
00:31:43.053 --> 00:31:44.948
- Do something for her!
- We've given her as much

410
00:31:44.972 --> 00:31:46.546
milk of the poppy as we can

411
00:31:46.571 --> 00:31:47.965
without risking the child.

412
00:31:47.989 --> 00:31:49.749
Your Queen is a strong woman.

413
00:31:49.774 --> 00:31:51.275
She's fighting with all her might.

414
00:31:51.359 --> 00:31:53.036
but it may not be enough.

415
00:31:53.191 --> 00:31:54.847
No!

416
00:31:54.871 --> 00:31:56.248
Aemma.

417
00:31:57.566 --> 00:31:59.727
Aemma... I'm here.

418
00:31:59.751 --> 00:32:02.113
- I'm here.
- Help me. please...

419
00:32:02.137 --> 00:32:04.190
I'm here. It's all right.

420
00:32:04.214 --> 00:32:06.234
- It's all right.
- I don't wanna do this.

421
00:32:06.258 --> 00:32:08.394
You're going to be all right.

422
00:32:08.418 --> 00:32:10.470
You're going to be all right.

423
00:32:35.170 --> 00:32:36.538
Kill him!

424
00:32:36.563 --> 00:32:38.774
And the day grows ugly.

425
00:32:43.001 --> 00:32:44.272
I wonder if this is how we should

426
00:32:44.296 --> 00:32:46.598
celebrate the birth of our future king.

427
00:32:46.622 --> 00:32:49.068
- Hm.
- With wanton violence.

428
00:32:49.092 --> 00:32:51.404
It's been 70
years since King Maegor's end.

429
00:32:51.428 --> 00:32:53.229
These knights are as green
as summer grass.

430
00:32:53.253 --> 00:32:54.848
None have known real war.

431
00:32:55.891 --> 00:32:57.842
Their lords sent them
to the tourney field

432
00:32:57.925 --> 00:33:00.621
with fists full of steel
and balls full of seed.

433
00:33:00.645 --> 00:33:03.023
and we expect them to act
with honor and grace.

434
00:33:03.340 --> 00:33:05.901
It's a marvel that war didn't
break out at first blood.

435
00:33:28.804 --> 00:33:29.931
Mellos.

436
00:33:31.140 --> 00:33:32.183
Your Grace.

437
00:33:33.613 --> 00:33:34.698
If you would.

438
00:33:44.904 --> 00:33:46.572
During a difficult birth.

439
00:33:46.656 --> 00:33:50.910
it sometimes becomes necessary
for the father...

440
00:33:51.869 --> 00:33:53.746
to make an impossible choice.

441
00:33:55.116 --> 00:33:56.409
Well. speak it.

442
00:33:56.977 --> 00:33:59.016
To sacrifice one...

443
00:33:59.329 --> 00:34:01.337
or to lose them both.

444
00:34:02.691 --> 00:34:05.669
There is a chance that
we can save the child.

445
00:34:05.841 --> 00:34:07.885
A technique is taught at the Citadel.

446
00:34:07.969 --> 00:34:10.369
which involves cutting
directly into the womb

447
00:34:10.423 --> 00:34:11.931
to free the infant.

448
00:34:12.014 --> 00:34:15.136
- But the resulting blood loss...
- Seven Hells. Mellos.

449
00:34:27.274 --> 00:34:29.134
You can save the child?

450
00:34:29.615 --> 00:34:33.494
We must either act now
or leave it with the gods.

451
00:34:45.256 --> 00:34:48.495
Ser Criston Cole will now tilt against

452
00:34:48.520 --> 00:34:52.312
Ser Daemon Targaryen.
Prince of the City!

453
00:36:03.793 --> 00:36:05.747
- Viserys.
- Yes?

454
00:36:07.952 --> 00:36:09.859
They're going to bring the babe out now.

455
00:36:11.903 --> 00:36:13.177
Mm.

456
00:36:33.656 --> 00:36:35.176
I love you.

457
00:36:39.784 --> 00:36:40.951
Ooh.

458
00:36:42.998 --> 00:36:45.311
- What is happening?
- No. it's all right.

459
00:36:45.495 --> 00:36:48.356
No... what is happening?

460
00:36:49.233 --> 00:36:51.601
- Viserys. what...
- No. it's all right.

461
00:36:51.626 --> 00:36:52.978
- Wh-what are you doing?
- They're going to bring the babe out.

462
00:36:53.002 --> 00:36:54.146
How are they...

463
00:36:54.170 --> 00:36:55.856
- It's all right.
- Viserys. please.

464
00:36:55.880 --> 00:36:58.033
- It's all right.
- No. I'm scared. Not in...

465
00:36:58.058 --> 00:36:59.777
- Don't be scared.
- What is happening?

466
00:36:59.801 --> 00:37:01.904
Don't be scared.
They're going to bring the babe out.

467
00:37:01.928 --> 00:37:03.872
- Oh no.
- It's all right.

468
00:37:04.142 --> 00:37:06.060
They're going to bring the babe out.

469
00:37:07.434 --> 00:37:10.061
No! No! No!

470
00:37:10.145 --> 00:37:13.290
- I'm making the first incision.
- No. no. no!

471
00:37:13.314 --> 00:37:16.901
Viserys. no! Please!

472
00:37:17.694 --> 00:37:20.071
- No. no. no!
- Don't be scared.

473
00:37:43.817 --> 00:37:45.430
Sword!

474
00:37:45.513 --> 00:37:47.244
Prince Daemon Targaryen

475
00:37:47.269 --> 00:37:50.685
wishes to continue in a contest of arms!

476
00:39:40.256 --> 00:39:41.725
Yield.

477
00:39:43.406 --> 00:39:44.424
Yield.

478
00:40:18.625 --> 00:40:20.936
Gods. He's Dornish.

479
00:40:20.960 --> 00:40:23.671
I was hoping to ask
for the Princess's favor.

480
00:40:35.481 --> 00:40:37.685
I wish you luck. Ser Criston.

481
00:40:38.311 --> 00:40:39.479
Princess.

482
00:40:50.930 --> 00:40:52.908
Congratulations. Your Grace.

483
00:40:53.737 --> 00:40:55.155
You have a son.

484
00:40:58.637 --> 00:41:00.583
It's a boy?

485
00:41:00.733 --> 00:41:02.877
A new heir. Your Grace.

486
00:41:08.779 --> 00:41:11.344
Had you and the Queen chosen a name?

487
00:41:15.003 --> 00:41:16.291
Baelon.

488
00:42:34.118 --> 00:42:36.079
They're waiting for you.

489
00:42:44.687 --> 00:42:47.471
_

490
00:42:48.812 --> 00:42:52.429
_

491
00:42:52.539 --> 00:42:54.240
_

492
00:42:55.490 --> 00:42:58.785
_

493
00:42:59.202 --> 00:43:00.995
_

494
00:43:15.053 --> 00:43:17.512
D...

495
00:43:31.875 --> 00:43:33.361
Dracarys.

496
00:44:12.504 --> 00:44:14.212
- Where's Rhaenyra?
- Your Grace.

497
00:44:14.292 --> 00:44:17.045
This is the last thing
any of us wish to discuss

498
00:44:17.113 --> 00:44:18.463
at this dark hour.

499
00:44:18.488 --> 00:44:20.384
but I consider the matter urgent.

500
00:44:20.408 --> 00:44:21.701
What matter?

501
00:44:22.764 --> 00:44:24.604
That of your succession.

502
00:44:25.121 --> 00:44:28.708
These recent tragedies have left
you without an obvious heir.

503
00:44:28.791 --> 00:44:30.643
The King has an heir. my Lord Hand.

504
00:44:30.668 --> 00:44:33.354
Despite how difficult this time
is. Your Grace.

505
00:44:33.379 --> 00:44:34.630
I feel it important

506
00:44:34.714 --> 00:44:36.507
the succession be firmly in place

507
00:44:36.598 --> 00:44:37.860
for the stability of the realm.

508
00:44:37.884 --> 00:44:39.821
The succession is already set...

509
00:44:40.052 --> 00:44:41.780
by precedent and by law.

510
00:44:41.804 --> 00:44:43.222
Shall we say his name?

511
00:44:45.792 --> 00:44:47.335
Daemon Targaryen.

512
00:44:47.419 --> 00:44:50.664
If Daemon were to remain
the uncontested heir.

513
00:44:50.688 --> 00:44:52.924
it could destabilize the realm.

514
00:44:53.008 --> 00:44:55.168
The realm? Or this council?

515
00:44:55.192 --> 00:44:58.297
No one here can know what
Daemon would do were he king.

516
00:44:58.321 --> 00:45:00.698
but no one can doubt his ambition.

517
00:45:00.848 --> 00:45:03.117
Look at what he did
with the gold cloaks.

518
00:45:03.352 --> 00:45:05.437
The City Watch is fiercely loyal to him.

519
00:45:05.520 --> 00:45:09.065
- An army 2.000 strong.
- An army you gave him. Otto.

520
00:45:09.398 --> 00:45:11.350
I named Daemon Master of Laws.

521
00:45:11.375 --> 00:45:12.985
but you said he was a tyrant.

522
00:45:13.361 --> 00:45:16.398
As Master of Coin.
you said he was a spendthrift

523
00:45:16.422 --> 00:45:17.691
that would beggar the realm.

524
00:45:17.715 --> 00:45:19.802
Putting Daemon in command
of the City Watch

525
00:45:19.826 --> 00:45:21.570
was your solution!

526
00:45:21.594 --> 00:45:23.739
A half-measure. Your Grace.

527
00:45:23.763 --> 00:45:27.034
The truth is. Daemon should
be far away from this court.

528
00:45:27.058 --> 00:45:28.559
Daemon is my brother.

529
00:45:28.752 --> 00:45:30.086
My blood.

530
00:45:30.937 --> 00:45:33.123
And he will have his place at my court.

531
00:45:33.147 --> 00:45:35.333
Let him keep his place at
court. Your Grace.

532
00:45:35.358 --> 00:45:37.376
but if the gods should visit

533
00:45:37.401 --> 00:45:39.713
some further tragedy on you.

534
00:45:39.737 --> 00:45:42.657
- either by design or by accident...
- "Design"?

535
00:45:43.182 --> 00:45:44.267
What are you saying?

536
00:45:44.559 --> 00:45:47.270
My brother would murder me.
take my crown?

537
00:45:48.521 --> 00:45:49.856
Are you?!

538
00:45:51.497 --> 00:45:52.817
Please.

539
00:45:53.582 --> 00:45:55.561
Daemon has ambition. yes.

540
00:45:55.586 --> 00:45:57.272
but not for the throne.

541
00:45:57.296 --> 00:45:59.031
He lacks the patience for it.

542
00:45:59.274 --> 00:46:01.251
The gods have yet to make a man who

543
00:46:01.284 --> 00:46:04.268
lacks the patience for absolute
power. Your Grace.

544
00:46:04.387 --> 00:46:06.139
Under such circumstances.

545
00:46:06.223 --> 00:46:08.617
it would not be an aberration

546
00:46:08.641 --> 00:46:11.036
for the King to name a successor.

547
00:46:11.060 --> 00:46:12.920
Well. who else would have a claim?

548
00:46:19.668 --> 00:46:21.755
The King's firstborn child.

549
00:46:21.779 --> 00:46:24.056
Rhaenyra? A girl?

550
00:46:25.808 --> 00:46:27.885
No queen has ever sat the Iron Throne.

551
00:46:27.910 --> 00:46:30.263
That is only by tradition
and precedent. Lord Strong.

552
00:46:30.287 --> 00:46:32.474
If order and stability
so concerns this council.

553
00:46:32.498 --> 00:46:36.144
then perhaps we shouldn't break 100
years of it by naming a girl heir.

554
00:46:36.168 --> 00:46:39.505
Daemon would be a second Maegor.
or worse.

555
00:46:40.114 --> 00:46:42.283
He is impulsive and violent.

556
00:46:42.658 --> 00:46:44.778
It is the duty of this council

557
00:46:44.802 --> 00:46:47.747
to protect the King
and the realm from him.

558
00:46:48.998 --> 00:46:51.701
I'm sorry. Your Grace.
but that is the truth as I see it.

559
00:46:51.725 --> 00:46:53.250
and I know that others here agree.

560
00:46:53.274 --> 00:46:55.205
I will not be made to choose

561
00:46:55.229 --> 00:46:57.165
between my brother and my daughter.

562
00:46:57.189 --> 00:46:58.917
You wouldn't have
to. Your Grace.

563
00:46:58.941 --> 00:47:01.336
There are others who would have a claim.

564
00:47:01.360 --> 00:47:03.422
Such as your wife. Lord Corlys?

565
00:47:03.446 --> 00:47:05.882
- "The Queen Who Never Was"?
- Rhaenys was the only child

566
00:47:05.906 --> 00:47:07.009
of Jaehaerys' eldest son.

567
00:47:07.033 --> 00:47:09.052
She had a strong claim
at the Great Council.

568
00:47:09.076 --> 00:47:10.929
and she already has a male heir.

569
00:47:10.953 --> 00:47:14.099
Just moments ago.
you announced your support for Daemon!

570
00:47:14.123 --> 00:47:15.976
If we cannot agree on an heir.
then how can we expect...

571
00:47:16.000 --> 00:47:17.652
My wife and son are dead!

572
00:47:19.278 --> 00:47:24.033
I will not sit here and suffer crows
that come to feast on their corpses!

573
00:47:57.750 --> 00:48:00.778
Send a raven to Old town. Straight away.

574
00:48:03.810 --> 00:48:05.065
My Lady.

575
00:48:15.564 --> 00:48:16.899
My darling.

576
00:48:25.886 --> 00:48:27.513
How's Rhaenyra?

577
00:48:30.297 --> 00:48:31.767
She lost her mother.

578
00:48:33.360 --> 00:48:35.855
The Queen was well-loved by all.

579
00:48:38.315 --> 00:48:41.360
I found myself thinking
of your own mother today.

580
00:48:47.950 --> 00:48:50.410
- How is His Grace?
- Very low.

581
00:48:52.112 --> 00:48:53.864
Which is why I sent for you.

582
00:48:59.086 --> 00:49:01.255
I thought you might go to him...

583
00:49:02.173 --> 00:49:03.758
offer him comfort.

584
00:49:06.177 --> 00:49:07.553
In his chambers?

585
00:49:14.118 --> 00:49:15.770
I wouldn't know what to say.

586
00:49:16.413 --> 00:49:17.772
Stop that.

587
00:49:19.815 --> 00:49:21.567
He'll be glad of a visitor.

588
00:49:29.943 --> 00:49:32.369
You might wear one of
your mother's dresses.

589
00:50:09.054 --> 00:50:11.450
The Lady Alicent High tower. Your Grace.

590
00:50:17.363 --> 00:50:19.041
What is it. Alicent?

591
00:50:19.518 --> 00:50:21.919
I thought I might come
and look in on you. Your Grace.

592
00:50:23.759 --> 00:50:24.897
I brought a book.

593
00:50:27.508 --> 00:50:29.568
That's very kind. thank you.

594
00:50:34.641 --> 00:50:36.033
It's a favorite of mine.

595
00:50:36.809 --> 00:50:39.270
I do know how passionate
you are for the histories.

596
00:50:40.813 --> 00:50:42.606
Yes... I am.

597
00:51:00.458 --> 00:51:01.835
When my mother died...

598
00:51:03.506 --> 00:51:05.588
people only ever spoke to me in riddles.

599
00:51:07.798 --> 00:51:10.110
All I wanted was for someone
to say that they were sorry

600
00:51:10.134 --> 00:51:11.510
for what happened to me.

601
00:51:15.642 --> 00:51:17.474
I'm very sorry. Your Grace.

602
00:52:05.648 --> 00:52:06.691
Thank you.

603
00:52:08.525 --> 00:52:11.237
The King's sole heir once again.

604
00:52:12.947 --> 00:52:15.883
Might we drink to our future?

605
00:52:15.908 --> 00:52:18.744
Quiet!

606
00:52:18.772 --> 00:52:21.205
Your Prince will speak!

607
00:52:25.065 --> 00:52:26.835
Silence!

608
00:52:32.691 --> 00:52:34.609
Before we begin. Your Grace.

609
00:52:34.693 --> 00:52:38.555
I have a report I feel
compelled to share.

610
00:52:40.824 --> 00:52:42.184
Last night...

611
00:52:42.768 --> 00:52:45.621
Prince Daemon bought out
one of the pleasure houses

612
00:52:45.646 --> 00:52:47.289
on the Street of Silk...

613
00:52:48.206 --> 00:52:51.654
to entertain officers of the City Watch

614
00:52:51.679 --> 00:52:53.279
and other friends of his.

615
00:52:56.712 --> 00:52:59.360
King and Council have
long rued my position

616
00:52:59.385 --> 00:53:01.153
as next in line for the throne.

617
00:53:02.721 --> 00:53:05.532
But dream and pray as they all might.

618
00:53:05.557 --> 00:53:08.185
it seems I'm not so easily replaced.

619
00:53:10.520 --> 00:53:13.148
The gods give just
as the gods take away.

620
00:53:13.231 --> 00:53:15.275
He toasted Prince Baelon.

621
00:53:15.358 --> 00:53:16.593
To the King's son.

622
00:53:17.303 --> 00:53:19.013
Styling him...

623
00:53:20.097 --> 00:53:22.599
"The Heir for a Day."

624
00:53:29.356 --> 00:53:31.374
I corroborated this report

625
00:53:31.458 --> 00:53:33.857
with three separate witnesses.

626
00:53:33.882 --> 00:53:37.684
The evening was. by all accounts a...
celebration.

627
00:53:40.091 --> 00:53:42.636
You cut the
image of the conqueror. brother.

628
00:53:44.371 --> 00:53:45.889
Did you say it?

629
00:53:47.974 --> 00:53:49.619
I don't know what you mean.

630
00:53:49.643 --> 00:53:51.423
You will address me as "Your Grace."

631
00:53:51.448 --> 00:53:54.298
or I will have my Kings guard
cut out your tongue.

632
00:53:57.801 --> 00:54:01.989
"The Heir for a Day." Did you say it?

633
00:54:11.724 --> 00:54:14.501
We must all mourn
in our own way. Your Grace.

634
00:54:16.169 --> 00:54:19.573
My family has just been destroyed.

635
00:54:20.574 --> 00:54:23.385
But instead of being
by my side. or Rhaenyra's.

636
00:54:23.760 --> 00:54:26.305
you chose to
celebrate your own rise!

637
00:54:26.561 --> 00:54:29.583
Laughing with your whores
and your lickspittles!

638
00:54:31.977 --> 00:54:34.671
You have no allies at court but me!

639
00:54:35.230 --> 00:54:37.524
I have only ever defended you!

640
00:54:37.774 --> 00:54:40.669
Yet everything I've given you.
you've thrown back in my face.

641
00:54:40.694 --> 00:54:42.671
You've only ever tried to send me away.

642
00:54:42.696 --> 00:54:45.198
To the Vale. to the City Watch.

643
00:54:45.282 --> 00:54:47.330
anywhere but by your side.

644
00:54:47.401 --> 00:54:49.587
Ten years you've been king.

645
00:54:49.612 --> 00:54:52.514
and yet not once have you
asked me to be your Hand!

646
00:54:52.539 --> 00:54:55.542
- Why would I do that?
- Because I'm your brother.

647
00:54:56.626 --> 00:54:58.795
And the blood of the dragon runs thick.

648
00:54:58.879 --> 00:55:01.066
Then why do you cut me so deeply?

649
00:55:01.098 --> 00:55:02.395
I've only ever spoken the truth.

650
00:55:02.419 --> 00:55:04.326
I see Otto High tower for what he is.

651
00:55:04.910 --> 00:55:07.596
- An unwavering and loyal Hand?
- A cunt.

652
00:55:08.914 --> 00:55:11.264
A second son who stands
to inherit nothing

653
00:55:11.288 --> 00:55:12.660
he doesn't seize for himself.

654
00:55:12.684 --> 00:55:15.038
Otto High tower is a more honorable man

655
00:55:15.062 --> 00:55:17.123
- than you could ever be.
- He doesn't protect you.

656
00:55:17.147 --> 00:55:18.715
- I would.
- From what?

657
00:55:19.049 --> 00:55:20.175
Yourself.

658
00:55:23.770 --> 00:55:26.406
You're weak... Viserys.

659
00:55:29.226 --> 00:55:30.970
And that council of leeches knows it.

660
00:55:30.994 --> 00:55:33.080
They all prey on you for their own ends.

661
00:55:37.834 --> 00:55:39.878
I have decided to name a new heir.

662
00:55:40.089 --> 00:55:42.614
- I'm your heir.
- Not anymore.

663
00:55:43.907 --> 00:55:47.094
You are to return to Runestone
and your lady wife at once.

664
00:55:47.636 --> 00:55:49.888
and you are to do so without quarrel

665
00:55:50.931 --> 00:55:53.167
by order of your King.

666
00:56:07.700 --> 00:56:09.116
Your Grace.

667
00:57:08.688 --> 00:57:09.772
Father.

668
00:57:14.027 --> 00:57:18.615
Balerion was the last living creature to
have seen Old Valyria before the Doom.

669
00:57:21.242 --> 00:57:23.507
Its greatness and its flaws.

670
00:57:23.953 --> 00:57:26.014
When you look at the dragons.
what do you see?

671
00:57:26.870 --> 00:57:27.870
What?

672
00:57:27.970 --> 00:57:30.757
You haven't spoken a word to me
since mother's funeral.

673
00:57:30.781 --> 00:57:33.510
- and now you send your Kings guard down...
- Answer me.

674
00:57:36.417 --> 00:57:37.663
It's important.

675
00:57:38.438 --> 00:57:39.873
What do you see?

676
00:57:47.716 --> 00:57:50.342
- I suppose I see us.
- Tell me.

677
00:57:51.410 --> 00:57:55.055
Everyone says Targaryens are
closer to gods than to men.

678
00:57:55.455 --> 00:57:58.166
but they say that
because of our dragons.

679
00:57:59.752 --> 00:58:01.878
Without them.
we're just like everyone else.

680
00:58:04.743 --> 00:58:08.343
The idea that we control the dragons...

681
00:58:08.802 --> 00:58:10.304
is an illusion.

682
00:58:12.180 --> 00:58:14.658
They're a power man should
never have trifled with.

683
00:58:16.702 --> 00:58:18.687
One that brought Valyria its doom.

684
00:58:19.313 --> 00:58:22.232
If we don't mind our own histories.
it will do the same to us.

685
00:58:23.191 --> 00:58:25.585
Targaryen must understand
this to be King...

686
00:58:27.237 --> 00:58:28.280
or Queen.

687
00:58:32.576 --> 00:58:34.119
I'm sorry. Rhaenyra.

688
00:58:35.245 --> 00:58:37.973
I have wasted the years
since you were born...

689
00:58:38.206 --> 00:58:39.875
wanting for a son.

690
00:58:52.051 --> 00:58:54.179
You are the very best of your mother.

691
00:58:57.142 --> 00:58:59.327
And I believe it. I know she did.

692
00:58:59.520 --> 00:59:01.647
that you could be a great ruling queen.

693
00:59:02.038 --> 00:59:03.649
Daemon is your heir.

694
00:59:05.116 --> 00:59:07.878
Daemon was
not made to wear the crown.

695
00:59:08.487 --> 00:59:10.155
But I believe that you were.

696
00:59:11.064 --> 00:59:13.776
Corlys of House Velaryon.

697
00:59:13.800 --> 00:59:18.030
Lord of the Tides
and Master of Driftmark.

698
00:59:18.054 --> 00:59:20.974
I. Corlys Velaryon.

699
00:59:21.391 --> 00:59:24.144
Lord of the Tides
and Master of Driftmark.

700
00:59:24.728 --> 00:59:26.964
promise to be faithful to King Viserys

701
00:59:27.047 --> 00:59:29.691
and his named heir.
the Princess Rhaenyra.

702
00:59:29.941 --> 00:59:31.568
I pledge fealty to them

703
00:59:32.152 --> 00:59:34.130
and shall defend them
against all enemies

704
00:59:34.154 --> 00:59:36.849
in good faith and without deceit.

705
00:59:41.019 --> 00:59:43.939
I swear this by the old gods
and the new.

706
00:59:46.855 --> 00:59:49.524
This is no
trivial gesture. Rhaenyra.

707
00:59:49.695 --> 00:59:51.362
A dragon's saddle is one thing.

708
00:59:51.838 --> 00:59:55.159
but the Iron Throne is the most
dangerous seat in the realm.

709
00:59:55.891 --> 00:59:58.053
I. Lord Hobert High tower.

710
00:59:58.078 --> 01:00:00.372
Beacon of the South.
Defender of the Citadel.

711
01:00:00.456 --> 01:00:01.957
and Voice of Old town.

712
01:00:02.041 --> 01:00:04.535
promise to be faithful to King Viserys

713
01:00:04.559 --> 01:00:07.646
and his named heir.
the Princess Rhaenyra.

714
01:00:10.507 --> 01:00:12.251
I pledge fealty to them

715
01:00:12.275 --> 01:00:14.319
and shall defend them
against all enemies

716
01:00:14.344 --> 01:00:16.905
in good faith and without deceit.

717
01:00:17.806 --> 01:00:20.100
I swear this by the old gods
and the new.

718
01:00:27.767 --> 01:00:29.143
Give me your hand.

719
01:00:43.803 --> 01:00:45.597
I. Boremund Baratheon...

720
01:00:47.002 --> 01:00:50.214
promise to be faithful
to King Viserys...

721
01:00:52.247 --> 01:00:55.026
There's something
else that I need to tell you.

722
01:00:55.844 --> 01:00:57.988
It might be difficult
for you to understand.

723
01:00:58.138 --> 01:00:59.781
but you must hear it.

724
01:01:00.682 --> 01:01:01.809
Our histories...

725
01:01:02.242 --> 01:01:05.287
they tell us that Aegon looked across
the Blackwater from Dragons tone.

726
01:01:05.495 --> 01:01:07.956
and saw a rich land
ripe for the capture.

727
01:01:09.464 --> 01:01:12.168
But ambition alone is not
what drove him to conquest.

728
01:01:13.396 --> 01:01:14.480
It was a dream.

729
01:01:15.255 --> 01:01:17.950
And just as Daenys foresaw
the end of Valyria.

730
01:01:18.033 --> 01:01:20.510
Aegon foresaw the end
of the world of men.

731
01:01:21.217 --> 01:01:23.678
'Tis to begin
with a terrible winter

732
01:01:24.222 --> 01:01:26.474
gusting out of the distant north.

733
01:01:26.875 --> 01:01:28.710
I. Rick on Stark.

734
01:01:28.794 --> 01:01:29.912
Lord of Winter fell...

735
01:01:29.936 --> 01:01:31.917
Aegon saw absolute darkness

736
01:01:31.942 --> 01:01:33.457
riding on those winds.

737
01:01:33.481 --> 01:01:35.084
And whatever dwells within

738
01:01:35.108 --> 01:01:36.943
will destroy the world of the living.

739
01:01:37.611 --> 01:01:39.942
When this Great Winter
comes. Rhaenyra...

740
01:01:40.986 --> 01:01:43.283
all of Westeros must stand against it.

741
01:01:43.809 --> 01:01:45.394
And if the world of men is to survive.

742
01:01:45.477 --> 01:01:48.038
a Targaryen must be seated
on the Iron Throne.

743
01:01:48.288 --> 01:01:49.664
A king or queen.

744
01:01:49.885 --> 01:01:51.442
strong enough to unite the realm

745
01:01:51.525 --> 01:01:53.752
against the cold and the dark.

746
01:01:56.111 --> 01:01:59.241
Aegon called his dream
"The Song of Ice and Fire."

747
01:02:01.660 --> 01:02:03.203
This secret...

748
01:02:04.204 --> 01:02:07.015
it's been passed from king
to heir since Aegon's time.

749
01:02:08.732 --> 01:02:10.750
Now you must promise to carry it...

750
01:02:11.630 --> 01:02:13.188
and protect it.

751
01:02:16.034 --> 01:02:17.801
Promise me this. Rhaenyra.

752
01:02:22.269 --> 01:02:23.448
Promise me.

753
01:02:29.329 --> 01:02:34.776
I. Viserys Targaryen.
first of his name...

754
01:02:36.487 --> 01:02:38.864
King of the Andals. and the Rhoynar.

755
01:02:39.072 --> 01:02:40.340
and the First Men.

756
01:02:41.091 --> 01:02:43.235
Lord of the Seven Kingdoms.

757
01:02:43.259 --> 01:02:45.178
and Protector of the Realm.

758
01:02:46.307 --> 01:02:47.847
do hereby name...

759
01:02:48.624 --> 01:02:50.451
Rhaenyra Targaryen

760
01:02:50.475 --> 01:02:52.644
Princess of Dragons tone

761
01:02:52.846 --> 01:02:55.512
and heir to the Iron Throne.

762
